args:
Dear Bro, Dear Sis,
Thanks for the letter! Glad you're doing well.
My chef training at the Halidom is continuing
pretty much like always, I guess.

I know it's tough to keep the restaurant running,
and I'm sorry. It's mostly my fault, after all,
seeing as how I wasn't able to live up to
the expectations Dad had for me.

I want to become a chef even greater than him—
No, I HAVE to. So I'm going to keep working at
it day and night. Until then, good luck!
—Mitsuba
Gah! Noelle?! How long\nhave you been here?!
Um, a few minutes? Sorry! I knocked and\nyou answered, so I...came in.
...You did? Huh. Honestly, I was so\nabsorbed in my letter that I must have\nresponded without even realizing it.
Um, r-right. Well, I'm heading up north\ntomorrow, so if you have any letters or\nthings to send, I can, um...collect them?
The work of a messenger really never\nends, huh? But yeah, I've got something \nfor you if it's not too much trouble.
Besides, my letters have been arriving\nfaster lately if I send them through North\nGrastaea.
I think that's how it is this time of year.\nTrade with neighboring countries gets\nmore active before all the...um...snow.
Still, it sounds like you want it delivered\nfast. Is something the matter?
Oh, just the family business not doing\nso hot again. Same old, same old.
They could really use me in the kitchen,\nbut I'm all the way over here training to\nbecome a better chef. It's...hard.
Your family business is, um...\na restaurant, right?
That's right, a place called Nanakusa. One\nof the fanciest joints in all of Hinomoto.

My sister helps out, but she runs another
restaurant and can only do so much.
Honestly, we're in deep trouble if we
can't restore the reputation my father had.
And I'm the second-generation head chef,\nso it's up to me to make that happen.
Don't be so hard on yourself, Mitsuba!

I mean, there isn't much of a choice here.
If I want to surpass Dad and give his
customers the experience they want,
I have to carve my own path as a chef.
So that means practice and work\nday and night without pause!
*yawn* ...Hmm? What's all this food\ndoing here so early in the morning?
Hello, Mitsuba. I assume I have you to\nthank for this veritable mountain of food?
Yeah, there were a few dishes I wanted\nto try out, so I made breakfast.
This is less ＂a few dishes＂ and more of a\nbanquet. Were you cooking all night long?
So what Noelle told me was true.

She came to me before she set out and
told me how you are tormenting yourself
about your family restaurant. She then
asked for me to check in on you.
I understand your situation, but you'll not\nget anywhere if you put such pressure on\nyourself without end.
No buts. Let me instead ask you this:\nWhat did you achieve from staying up\nall night cooking?
You'll do your family no good if you\nend up working yourself to death.
In fact, the time I most recently saw your\ncooking shine is when we were roasting\nfiends outdoors with Pecorine.
Surely it would be better training to cook\nin a relaxed fashion such as that?
Come to think of it, you're right...\nI was really in the zone back there.
It made me feel like my cooking was...\nI dunno. Worthwhile, I guess?
Agreed. Pecorine may have savored eating\nthe food, but making it was also fun in its\nown right.
Are you all right, Mitsuba?\nI lost you there for a moment.
Would you head into the mountains\nwith me so we can cook outdoors?
Well, it's doesn't have to be mountains,\nspecifically. Anywhere outside is fine.
If I can just experience the sense of worth\nI did while I was camping, I think it might\nreally do me some good.

I can learn something I won't be able to
if I'm shut up in a kitchen—and maybe
even something that will finally let me
surpass Dad.
Er, we seem to be discussing two things\nrather far removed from each other...
(I feel like she raced right by my point\nabout letting the training go for a bit.)
(But perhaps this is just the change of\npace that Mitsuba needs.)
Very well. I will accompany you. In truth,\nI rather enjoyed our outdoor cooking\nadventure and would like to do it again.
Oh, thanks! I'm gonna go get ready!
(As ever, she is earnest and dedicated\nto her craft—perhaps TOO much so.)
(But can she really find what she needs for\na restaurant in the great outdo—)
Those are the camping clothes you wore\nlast time, yes? Goodness, but you got\nchanged quickly.
When I decide to do something, I DO it!\nNo point lollygagging around, right?
Anyway, we gotta shake the lead out,\nso go get changed! Go go gooooo!
Stop pushing me! I am going!
